name: Dallas Stars
summary: The Dallas Stars have advanced to the Western Conference Finals after defeating the Colorado Avalanche in Game 6 of their second-round series. The Stars, who finished the regular season with the third-best record in the West, have now eliminated the past two Stanley Cup champions, the Avalanche and the St. Louis Blues. The Stars will face the Edmonton Oilers in the Western Conference Finals, which begin on Saturday. The Oilers, who upset the Calgary Flames in the first round, advanced to the Western Conference Finals for the first time since 2006.

summary: Former Baltimore City State's Attorney Marilyn Mosby has been sentenced after being found guilty of perjury and mortgage fraud. The sentencing hearing took place on Thursday, and the judge ordered her to forfeit her condo. Mosby had previously sought a pardon ahead of the sentencing, but her request was denied. Instead, she received a probation sentence and community service as part of her punishment. Despite being spared prison time, Mosby has faced criticism and calls for her to resign from her office.

summary: Ebrahim Raisi, the hardline Iranian president and protege of Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei, has died at the age of 63 in a helicopter crash. Raisi, known for his brutal crackdowns on political opposition and his grim human rights record, became president in 2021. His death has sparked an investigation, and Iran has begun days of funeral ceremonies. Raisi's death leaves a void in Iran's political landscape, and observers are speculating about his successor. Amnesty International has called for accountability for Raisi's human rights violations, while others are considering the implications of his death for Iran's regional and international relations.

name: Memorial Day meaning
summary: Memorial Day, a federal holiday, commemorates the fallen American soldiers who have died while serving in the military. Observed on the last Monday of May, its meaning extends beyond a three-day weekend. It serves as a reminder to honor and pay tribute to the sacrifices made by those brave individuals. This year, it will be observed on May 27th, 2024. Some voices advocate for an overhaul of federal holidays, including Memorial Day, to ensure their continued relevance and alignment with contemporary values and priorities.
